Feature Branches:  ⭐
feature/branch-name: Used for adding new features or functionalities.
Examples: 
  feature/user-authentication
  feature/payment-integration

Bug Fix Branches: 🪲
bugfix/branch-name: Used for fixing bugs or issues.
Examples: 
  bugfix/database-error
  bugfix/ui-styling-issue

Hotfix Branches: 🔥
Hotfix/branch-name: Used for critical fixes that need to be deployed quickly.
Examples: 
  hotfix/security-issue
  hotfix/crash-fix

Personal Branches: 👨‍💻
user/username/branch-name: Individual branches for personal work.
Examples: 
  user/johndoe/experimental-feature
  user/janedoe/bugfix-login

Documentation Branches: 📄
doc/documentation-topic: Used for documentation changes.
Examples: 
  doc/update-readme
  doc/api-documentation

Release Branches: 📬 
release/version-number: Used to prepare for a new release version.
Examples: 
  release/1.0.0
  release/2.1.3
 
NOTE:
Keep branch names concise, but descriptive enough to understand their purpose.
Use lowercase letters and hyphens for better readability.
Avoid spaces, special characters, and accents.
